                                    <img src="dist/images/bodys-tale-of-vengeance-mercy/img-method1.png" class="w100">
                                </figure>
                                <b class="fserif">C. Freewriting the Script</b><br><br>
                                <p>After using the journey as an metaphor for our healing path, the memeber starts its freewriting session. Here's the prompt:</p>
                                <blockquote class="mb40">As you, the hero, decide to take action, what happens in the 24 hours before and after that pivotal moment of action?</blockquote>
                                <p>Freewriting means writing continuously—without worrying about perfection. Whatever thoughts come to mind, keep them flowing. The key is not to stop.</p>
                                <blockquote class="mb40">
                                    TT then guides everyone into a meditative state before the writing begins:<br>
                                    — TT<br><br>

                                    "Now, please sit comfortably and relax your body. Close your eyes, and focus on your breathing—slowly inhale and exhale, feeling your body gradually relax.<br><br>

                                    Next, let's enter the setting of your revenge script. You've been gathering friends or resources, practicing, and finally taking action. Imagine the 24 hours before and after this moment. Picture the space you're in. What does it look like? Try to see every detail—colors, light, where objects are placed. What do you observe?<br><br>

                                    Now, notice the temperature of the air—warm or cold? Can you smell anything? Perhaps a familiar scent or one that feels oppressive? Listen to the sounds around you—footsteps, wind, or other subtle noises. Envision yourself truly hearing these sounds in your scene.<br>
                                    Finally, notice what emotions arise—'anger,' 'disappointment,' 'determination'? How does your body react in this moment? Are your muscles tense or relaxed? What feelings surface inside you? Let these sensations flow freely without trying to suppress or control them.<br>
                                    When you're ready, express everything you've just seen, heard, smelled, and felt in writing—descriptions of the environment, your inner emotions, anything—and weave it into your script."
                                </blockquote>
